{"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Bytes","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"Bytes","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Bytes","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib5BytesC","symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A simple reference counted data type representing an immutable sequence of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"zero or more bytes from an unspecified origin."}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/BytesProtocol","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Bytes","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The purpose of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" is to keep the memory region that it holds"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"alive for as long as anyone holds a reference to the bytes.  When","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the last reference count is dropped, the memory is released. Multiple"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unrelated callers can use byte data in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" without coordinating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their activities, resting assured that the byte data will not change or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"move while they hold a reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" can come from many different origins that may have","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"different procedures for freeing the memory region.  Examples are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"memory from [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.malloc"},{"text":"], from memory slices, from a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MappedFile"},{"text":"] or memory from other allocators.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" work well as keys in [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashTable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]. Use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.Bytes.equal","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"code":"GLib.Bytes.hash","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] as parameters to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.HashTable.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] or [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.HashTable.new_full","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be used as keys in a [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Tree","isActive":true},{"text":"] by passing the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Bytes.compare"},{"type":"text","text":"] function to [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Tree.new"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The data pointed to by this bytes must not be modified. For a mutable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"array of bytes see 